quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,93,"And assuredly We settled the Children of Isra'il into a secure settlement, and We provided them with good things; nor they differed until there had come unto them the knowledge. Verily thine Lord shall judge between them on the Day of Resurrection as to that wherein they have been differing"
  10,94,"And if thou be in doubt concerning that which We have sent down unto thee, then ask those who have read the Books before thee. Assuredly hath the truth come unto thee from thy Lord, so be not then of the doubters"
  10,95,"And be not thou of those who belie Allah's signs, lest thou be of the losers"
  10,96,Verily those on whom the word of thy Lord hath been justified shall not believe
  10,97,"Even though every sign should come unto them, until they hehold an afflictive torment"
  10,98,"Why then was there not a township which believed, so that its faith might have profited it, except the people of Yunus! When they believed, We removed from them the torment of humiliation in the life of the world, and We let them enjoy for a season"
  10,99,"And had thy Lord willed, those who are on the earth would have believed, all of them, together; canst thou then compel mankind until they become believers"
  10,100,"It is not for any soul that it should believe save with Allah's will, and He layeth the abomination upon those who reflect not"
  10,101,"Say thou: behold that which is in the heavens and the earth; and signs and warnings avail not those who will not believe"
  10,102,"Wait they then aught but the days of those who have passed away before them. Say thou: wait then, verily I am with you among those who wait"
  10,103,"Thereafter We delivered Our apostles and those who believed. Even so, as incumbent upon us, We deliver the believers"